The Shanghai-Nantong Yangtze River Bridge is under construction in Nantong, East China's Jiangsu Province on Monday. The 11.07-kilometer-long bridge, now known as the Hutong bridge, will function as a major link to integrate big cities in the Yangtze River Delta. It is expected to open to traffic in 2020. Photo: VCG  
